			<CASNumber>7647-01-0</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Hydrogen chloride is a hydrogen halide with the chemical formula HCl. At room temperature, it is a colourless gas, which forms white fumes of hydrochloric acid upon contact with atmospheric water vapor. It may be formed by the direct combination of chlorine (Cl 2) gas and hydrogen (H 2) gas. It can irritate the skin, nose, eyes, throat, and larynx. Exposure to liquid hydrogen chloride may cause frostbite.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氯化氢是一种卤化氢，化学式为 HCl。在室温下，它是一种无色气体，与大气中的水蒸气接触后会形成白色的盐酸烟雾。它可由氯气（Cl 2）和氢气（H 2）直接结合形成。它会刺激皮肤、鼻子、眼睛、喉咙和咽喉。接触液态氯化氢可能会导致冻伤。</common:generalComment>
